Class TesterClasses.Conversion_T2Q_Tester<S>

    Enclosing class:
    TesterClasses

    abstract static class TesterClasses.Conversion_T2Q_Tester<S>
extends TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<S,Quadruple>
    An abstract tester class whose descendants perform testing of conversions from other types to Quadruple, like Quadruple.Quadruple(String) or Quadruple.Quadruple(double).

    Implements protected methods:
    • TesterClasses.QuadTester.testOp(String[]) -- performs the tested operation and registers the result in the TestResults instance stored in the corresponding field.
    • TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester.otherTypeName() -- returns the simple name of the input type of the tested conversion.
    • TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester.performOp(Object) -- performs the tested conversion by creating a new instance of Quadruple via call to a constructor with appropriate type of the argument, depending on the source type.

    Defines abstract parseSrcType(String) method whose implementations provided by the descendants should return a value of the source type expressed by the input string from the data sample.

      • testOp

        protected void testOp(String[] dataSample)
        Tests a conversion from type S to Quadruple.
        Creates DataItem instances for the source value of type S from the data sample and for the same value expressed as Quadruple and BigDecimal values, performs the tested operation and creates a DataItem with the result, creates a DataItem with the expected value of the result, then registers the result in the TestResults instance stored in the corresponding field using its TestResults.record(DataItem, DataItem, DataItem, DataItem) method.
        Specified by:
        testOp in class TesterClasses.QuadTester
        Parameters:
        dataSample - an array containing String representations of the input argument(s) of the tested operation and a string representation of the expected result
